close_reason: Added embedding identity migration guidance across reindex and health surfaces.
body: "## Context\n\n`src/core/search/cache.ts:471-476`:\n```ts\nif (ledgerRead.embedding && hasVectorizationEmbeddingIdentityChanged(ledgerRead.embedding, embeddingIdentity)) {\n  return { refreshed: [], skipped: ..., warnings: ['search_semantic_refresh_requires_reindex:embedding_identity_changed'] };\n}\n```\n\nThis warning is emitted silently into the background worker output (not surfaced to the user on mutation). The user only discovers the problem when `pm health` shows `stale_items_before_total > 0` or when search quality degrades after a provider switch.\n\n`pm reindex` already resets the vector store and re-embeds everything, but the user must know to run it. There is no auto-detect on the mismatch that triggers a user-visible prompt or automated action.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] `pm health` surfaces a specific warning when `embedding_identity_changed` is detected (not just advisory)\n- [ ] `pm reindex` detects the identity mismatch and prompts/warns: 'Provider or model has changed since last index. Run pm reindex --mode semantic to rebuild.'\n- [ ] OR add `pm reindex --auto-migrate` that detects the mismatch and runs automatically\n- [ ] Document the provider-switch workflow in COMMANDS.md / AGENT_GUIDE\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `src/core/search/cache.ts:471-476` — silent skip on identity change\n- `src/core/search/vectorization-metadata.ts:62-67` — `hasVectorizationEmbeddingIdentityChanged` — the check exists but its output is only a background warning\n- `src/cli/commands/reindex.ts` — no identity-mismatch check before starting"
